  "body": "Does hardhat support rename a library with specific version in hardhat.config.js? Like brownie can set remappings in brownie-config.yaml as below:\r\n```yaml\r\ncompiler:\r\n  solc:\r\n    version: 0.5.17\r\n    remappings:\r\n      - \"@openzeppelinV2=OpenZeppelin/openzeppelin-contracts@2.5.1\"\r\n      - \"@openzeppelinV3=OpenZeppelin/openzeppelin-contracts@3.1.0\"\r\n```\r\n\r\nthen use it in solidity file:\r\n```solidity\r\nimport \"@openzeppelinV2/contracts/token/ERC20/IERC20.sol\";\r\n```\r\n",
