    "body": "@gzliudan while Hardhat doesn't support this (and I don't think we will, at least it's not in our plans), you can use [npm aliases](https://stackoverflow.com/a/56495651) to do that. It goes like this:\r\n\r\n```\r\nnpm i oz3@npm:@openzeppelin/contracts@3.4.1\r\nnpm i oz4@npm:@openzeppelin/contracts@4.2.0\r\n```\r\n\r\nAnd then in your contracts you can do this:\r\n\r\n```solidity\r\nimport \"oz3/token/ERC20/ERC20.sol\";\r\nimport \"oz4/token/ERC721/ERC721.sol\";\r\n```\r\n\r\nI hope that helps!",
